article.headline: Sam Houston St. 89, Texas-San Antonio 67
article.story: HUNTSVILLE, Texas -- Corey Allmond scored 20 points and Barkley Falkner pulled down 16 rebounds to go with 12 points to lead Sam Houston State to an 89-67 victory over Texas-San Antonio on Saturday. Five players reached double figures for the Bearkats (15-10, 9-3 Southland) in the game. Drae Murray scored 11 points off the bench, Preston Brown scored 11 and DeLuis Ramirez added 10 points. Devin Gibson led the Roadrunners (16-9, 7-5) with 17 points off the bench. Gibson was 11-of-12 from the free throw line and 3-of-12 from field goal range. Joey Shank scored 14 points for UTSA and Chris Allen added 12. Sam Houston State dominated in the paint where they outscored the Roadrunners 44-22.
